The paper deals with document analysis and word spotting using convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the confidence of the neural network in its predictions, which is a topic related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper explores different metrics for quantifying confidence, which is a topic related to natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM).
